               <birth when="1844">He was born at <placeName ref="LOC1465Ankoba"/> in <date>1844</date>. </birth>
               <floruit notBefore="1860" notAfter="1913">Mǝnilǝk is regarded as the founder of modern Ethiopian state. 
                  After the death of his father king <persName ref="PRS5205haylaMa"/>,   
                  in the course of the newly proclaimed king <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/>, in <date>1855</date>, Mǝnilǝk then aged 11, 
                  was taken into captivity into imperial court at <placeName ref="LOC4547Maqdal"/>. Here he was treated with much respect, and married
                  to <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/>'s daughter <persName ref="PRS1771AltasTe"/>. In <date>1865</date>, as the emperor power waned, 
                  Mǝnilǝk escaped from <placeName ref="LOC4547Maqdal"/> and was received with joy in <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa"/> as its rightful king. 
                  During the period from <date>1878</date>until <date>1889</date>, Mǝnilǝk  was a quasi independent ruler of  <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa"/>, 
                  he laid a foundations of his subsequent rule as emperor. 
                  
                 
               </floruit>
